Definition: uninterrupted in time and indefinitely long continuing
Example: the ceaseless thunder of surf; in constant pain; night and day we live with the incessant noise of the city; the never-ending search for happiness; the perpetual struggle to maintain standards in a democracy; man's unceasing warfare with drought and isolation; unremitting demands of hunger
Synonyms: noun, attribute, ceaselessness, constant, incessant, incessantness, incessancy, never-ending, perpetual, perpetuity, unceasing, unremitting, uninterrupted, in, time, and, indefinitely, long, continuing, the, thunder, of, surf, pain, night, day, we, live, with, noise, city, search, for, happiness, struggle, to, maintain, standards, a, democracy, man, s, warfare, drought, isolation, demands, hunger
Category: adj.all
